    <patterns>
      <pattern>Multipart form data in Minimal API: use `IFormFile file = context.Request.Form.Files["file"]` via `IFormFileCollection` bound via parameter binding — check existing multipart patterns in the codebase</pattern>
      <pattern>Redis TTL for session-scoped data: `_cache.SetAsync(key, data, new DistributedCacheEntryOptions { AbsoluteExpirationRelativeToNow = TimeSpan.FromHours(4) })`</pattern>
      <pattern>ProblemDetails for validation errors: `TypedResults.Problem(detail: "...", statusCode: 422, title: "Unprocessable Entity")` from Microsoft.AspNetCore.Http</pattern>
      <pattern>Redis key pattern: `doc-upload:{sessionId}:{documentId}` — sessionId scoping ensures auto-cleanup when session TTL expires</pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Users need to bring their own documents into SprkChat conversations — not just documents already
      in the matter's SPE container. This endpoint accepts arbitrary file uploads, extracts text via
      Document Intelligence (the same infrastructure already used for SPE documents), stores the extracted
      content in session-scoped Redis, and hands off to DocumentContextService for context injection.

      Session-scoped storage (NFR-06) is a security and privacy requirement: uploaded documents should
      not persist beyond the chat session. Redis TTL-based expiry is the correct mechanism — no cleanup
      job or event needed.

      The endpoint returns `202 Accepted` with a processing status because Document Intelligence can
      take several seconds for large documents. The `status` field may be `"processing"` initially,
      and the client can poll or receive the final status via SSE. For simplicity in R2, processing
      is synchronous (await the extraction) and always returns `"ready"` in the response. The async
      polling pattern is deferred to a future iteration.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      Depends on Task R2-011 (DocumentContextService). Safe to run in parallel with R2-012 and all
      Group B tasks. Task R2-014 (SPE persistence) depends on this task. Own files: new upload endpoint
      handler in `Api/Ai/ChatEndpoints.cs` (upload section) or a new `ChatDocumentEndpoints.cs` file.
    </dependencies>
  </context>

