    <step order="4">Implement Document Intelligence text extraction via the existing extractor service (reuse, do not re-implement)</step>
    <step order="5">Generate a GUID `documentId` for the uploaded file</step>
    <step order="6">Store extracted text in Redis with key `doc-upload:{sessionId}:{documentId}` and 4-hour TTL</step>
    <step order="7">Call `DocumentContextService.InjectDocumentContextAsync` to pre-warm the chunk index</step>
    <step order="8">Return `202 Accepted` with the document metadata response body (documentId, filename, status, pageCount, tokenEstimate, wasTruncated)</step>
    <step order="9">Apply authorization endpoint filter for session ownership</step>
    <step order="10">Apply upload-specific rate limit (5 uploads/minute/user)</step>
    <step order="11">Register the new endpoint in the application endpoint registration (likely in `Program.cs` or route group registration)</step>
    <step order="12">Run `dotnet build` and verify no errors</step>
    <step order="13">Update TASK-INDEX.md: change task R2-013 status to completed (🔲 → ✅)</step>
  </steps>

