  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{sessionId}/documents` with a valid PDF returns `202 Accepted` with documentId in the response body</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Uploading a .exe or .zip file returns `422 Unprocessable Entity` with a ProblemDetails body</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Uploading a file &gt; 50MB returns `413 Request Entity Too Large`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">After upload, the Redis key `doc-upload:{sessionId}:{documentId}` exists with a TTL between 3.5 and 4 hours</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Calling the endpoint without a valid session authorization returns `401 Unauthorized` from the endpoint filter</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">A 50-page PDF is processed (text extracted) within 15 seconds (NFR-02)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No extracted text content appears in application logs (ADR-015)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Sending 6 upload requests within one minute from the same user triggers rate limiting with `429 Too Many Requests` on the 6th request</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`dotnet build` passes with no errors</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    For the multipart form data binding in Minimal API, check whether the project already has a
    multipart binding helper or if `IFormFile` parameter binding is enabled via
    `builder.Services.AddAntiforgery()` or similar. If not enabled globally, add it scoped to this
    endpoint only.

    The 15-second NFR-02 target for Document Intelligence applies to documents under 50 pages. Larger
    documents (the upload limit is 50MB which could be hundreds of pages) may exceed this. Add a
    configurable timeout with a graceful `504 Gateway Timeout` `ProblemDetails` response if Document
    Intelligence does not respond within the configured limit (default 30 seconds for this endpoint).

    Document this endpoint's behavior in `notes/013-document-upload-endpoint.md` for the frontend
    tasks (R2-040, R2-041) that will implement the drag-and-drop upload UI.
  </notes>

